  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        True/False. For each of the following, write T if the statement is
        true; otherwise, write F. You do NOT need to provide explanations or show work for this problem. Throughout, let <m>G</m> and <m>G'</m> be groups.
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p>
              Every group contains at least two distinct subgroups.
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <p>
              If <m>H</m> is a proper subgroup of group <m>G</m> and <m>G</m> is finite, then we must have <m>|H|\lt |G|</m>.
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <p>
              <m>7\Z</m> is a subgroup of <m>14\Z</m>.
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <p>
              A group <m>G</m> may have two distinct proper subgroups which are isomorphic (to one another).
            </p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <solution>
    <p>
    <ol cols="4">
      <li>
        <p>
          F
        </p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <p>
          T
        </p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <p>
          F
        </p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <p>
          T
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
    </p>
  </solution>
